This paper discusses the use of cryptographic hash functions for data linking and the protection of privacy in the context of the Australian Bureau of Statistics. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of auxiliary data and the accuracy of data linking, which could also fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), machine learning (cs.LG), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
